Text.Value: Look at all those tads. Enough to make an army of Absolutists.
*There is no ledger to hint at a destination. Only a seal stamped on the lid, unknown to you.*

EditorData.SFXTags: [MO] VFX Support + Muffled squishy tadpole sound.
EditorData.VFXTags: [MO] Mindmeld on the Vat and/or Player (Loop)

Text.Value: *A mental churning as your interference stokes the tadpoles into a boiling frenzy. The connection snaps.*

EditorData.SFXTags: [MO] VFX Support + Muffled squishy tadpole sound.
EditorData.VFXTags: [MO] Mindmeld on the Vat and/or Player (Loop + Lead out) - Lead out should feel like a snap/woosh.

Text.Value: No. Annihilation is the only option.
It's not too late to stop the cult from using these things. Now's our chance to change them - or fry 'em.
*No ledger or shipping manifest presents itself - but there is a seal stamped on the lid.*

EditorData.SFXTags: [MO] VFX Support + Muffled squishy tadpole sound.
EditorData.VFXTags: [MO] Mindmeld on the Vat and/or Player (Loop)

Text.Value: Empty. Void of essence, void of purpose. We cannot allow their birth.
*The winged serpent of the Zhentarim - a network of merchant and mercenaries, known for their deep pockets and shallow scruples.*

EditorData.SFXTags: [MO] VFX Support + Muffled squishy tadpole sound.
EditorData.VFXTags: [MO] Mindmeld on the Vat and/or Player (Loop)

Text.Value: Look at them all... enough to infect an entire army.
*The winged serpent of the Zhentarim. It seems their pursuit of profit extends even here.*

EditorData.SFXTags: [MO] VFX Support + Muffled squishy tadpole sound.
EditorData.VFXTags: [MO] Mindmeld on the Vat and/or Player (Loop)

Text.Value: They came from below. We could destroy them, or perhaps...
Burn them, I say. Burn them all.
These tadpoles came from beneath the tower. If we use them, we'll deny the cultists of their power.
*A pattern of blank minds, newly born. They carry only a bare shred of memory, inherited from something older.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Player Mindmelding and sees a vision of the tadpoles squirming
EditorData.VFXTags: [MO] Mindmeld on the Vat and/or Player (Loop), , [MO] Start of vision and dark vignette

Text.Value: These tadpoles come from an ancient colony down below the tower. Whatever we do with them, we must deny their use to the Absolute.
*Your tadpole squirms and shrinks away - inside the vat is a churning mass you can do nothing to quell.*

EditorData.SFXTags: [MO] VFX Support + Muffled squishy tadpole sound.

Text.Value: *A wave of sick familiarity radiates from one barrel amidst the cargo.*

EditorData.SFXTags: [MO] VFX Support + Muffled squishy tadpole sound.
EditorData.VFXTags: [MO] Mindmeld on the Vat and/or Player (Lead In + Loop)

Text.Value: *Tadpoles. Sleeping and scarcely aware, but echoing yours a hundredfold.*

EditorData.SFXTags: [MO] VFX Support + Muffled squishy tadpole sound.
EditorData.VFXTags: [MO] Mindmeld on the Vat and/or Player (Loop)

Text.Value: Leave.
Holy hells. Each one, a mind flayer in waiting.
Examine the barrel.
*The winged serpent of the Zhentarim. These must be the 'goods' that Roah agreed to move into the city.*

EditorData.SFXTags: [MO] VFX Support + Muffled squishy tadpole sound.
EditorData.VFXTags: [MO] Mindmeld on the Vat and/or Player (Loop)

Text.Value: *The vat is still, placid - thousands of tadpoles happily awaiting their hosts.*

EditorData.SFXTags: [MO] VFX Support + Muffled squishy tadpole sound.

Text.Value: They don't know what they are - not yet. Unless we taught them to be something else...
*A sleep of centuries, the birth and destruction of a settlement above forming only background noise to the dream.*

EditorData.VFXTags: [MO] Mindmeld on the Vat and/or Player (Loop), , [MO] Loop of vision and dark vignette.

Text.Value: There's so many. Enough for an army of mindless slaves.

EditorData.NodeContext: Looking at a vat full of mind flayer tadpoles

Text.Value: *Until something descended down into the darkness... and the dreamer awoke.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Player, perturbed as mind-meld aura abruptly disappears
EditorData.VFXTags: [MO] Mindmeld on the Vat and/or Player (Loop + Lead out) - Lead out should feel like a snap/woosh., , [MO] End of Vision and Dark Vignette.

Text.Value: An army's worth of slithering parasites. Sickness, waiting to spread.
Reach out, tadpole-to-tadpole.
Examine the seal - it looks familiar to you.
*Your tadpole squirms, and feels a legion of echoes in response.*

EditorData.SFXTags: [MO] VFX Support + Muffled squishy tadpole sound.
EditorData.VFXTags: [MO] Mindmeld on the Vat and/or Player (Lead In + Loop)

Synopsis: The player has investigated the vat, showing thousands of tadpoles. They are being used to bolster their number of soldiers for their attack on Baldurs Gate. The player can destroy the Vat, depriving some of their numbers, or utter a phrase to influence whoever these tadpoles end up attached to.
